      <title type="html"><![CDATA[Kramdown's Markdown Attributes]]></title>
      <link href="http://vincenttam.github.io/blog/2014/09/14/kramdowns-markdown-attributes/"/>
    
    <updated>2014-09-14T16:37:49+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://vincenttam.github.io/blog/2014/09/14/kramdowns-markdown-attributes</id>
    
      <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>While writing a post about purging old Linux kernels, I made use of
<a href="http://fancyapps.com/fancybox/">fancybox</a>’s plugin to show a popup window which contains some <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr>
elements.<sup id="fnref:1"><a href="#fn:1" class="footnote">1</a></sup></p>

<p><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Original container for popup contents</span><a href='http://goo.gl/rdMWNf'>View raw </a></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='html'><span class='line'><span class="ni">&amp;lt;</span>div id=&quot;list1&quot; class=&quot;noscr&quot;<span class="ni">&amp;gt;</span><span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>The <span class="nt">&lt;strong&gt;</span>bolded<span class="nt">&lt;/strong&gt;</span> lines represent the packages that are
</span><span class='line'>going to be completely removed.<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="c">&lt;!-- omitted a pre tag --&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="ni">&amp;lt;</span>/div<span class="ni">&amp;gt;</span><span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;div</span> <span class="na">id=</span><span class="s">&quot;list2&quot;</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">&quot;noscr&quot;</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>There&#39;s <span class="nt">&lt;em&gt;</span>no<span class="nt">&lt;/em&gt;</span> lines beginning with <span class="nt">&lt;code&gt;</span>rc<span class="nt">&lt;/code&gt;</span>.<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="c">&lt;!-- omitted a pre tag --&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<p>I tried writing Markdown code inside these <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> containers, but the
Markdown code <em>failed</em> to be changed to <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr>.  As a result, <em>not</em>
being familiar with much of the Markdown syntax specified by
<a href="http://kramdown.gettalong.org/" title="fast, pure-Ruby Markdown-superset converter">kramdown</a>, I simply write <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr> inside these <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> elements.</p>

<p>Fancybox is great, but if I need to give up Markdown, then what’s the
point of overcoming so many technical problems related to Octopress?
<em>Without</em> <a href="http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/">Markdown</a> and <a href="http://www.vim.org"><abbr title="VIsual editor, iMproved">Vim</abbr></a>, blogging will be <em>incredibly</em>
difficult for me.  For the former, when compared with <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr>, it’s much
easier to read and write; for the latter, it offers an efficient text
editing experience.</p>

<p>Therefore, this afternoon, I browsed <em>kramdown Syntax</em> in kramdown’s
official website, and found out that the <code>markdown="1"</code> attribute can
solve this problem.<sup id="fnref:2"><a href="#fn:2" class="footnote">2</a></sup></p>

<p><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Current container for popup contents</span><a href='http://goo.gl/53zo2d'>View raw </a></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='html'><span class='line'><span class="ni">&amp;lt;</span>div id=&quot;list1&quot; class=&quot;noscr&quot; markdown=&quot;1&quot;<span class="ni">&amp;gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>The <span class="nt">&lt;strong&gt;</span>bolded<span class="nt">&lt;/strong&gt;</span> lines represent the packages that are going to be
</span><span class='line'>completely removed.
</span><span class='line'><span class="c">&lt;!-- omitted a pre tag --&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="ni">&amp;lt;</span>/div<span class="ni">&amp;gt;</span><span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;div</span> <span class="na">id=</span><span class="s">&quot;list2&quot;</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">&quot;noscr&quot;</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>There’s <span class="nt">&lt;em&gt;</span>no<span class="nt">&lt;/em&gt;</span> lines beginning with <span class="nt">&lt;code&gt;</span>rc<span class="nt">&lt;/code&gt;</span>.
</span><span class='line'><span class="c">&lt;!-- omitted a pre tag --&gt;</span><span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<hr />

<div class="footnotes">
  <ol>
    <li id="fn:1">
      <p><a href="/blog/2014/09/13/completely-remove-linux-kernels/"><em>Completely Remove Linux Kernels</em></a> in Blog 1. <a href="#fnref:1" class="reversefootnote">&#8617;</a></p>
    </li>
    <li id="fn:2">
      <p><a href="http://kramdown.gettalong.org/syntax.html#html-blocks">HTML Blocks</a> in <em>kramdown Syntax</em>. <a href="#fnref:2" class="reversefootnote">&#8617;</a></p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</div>
]]></content>
    
